<subSubSection pageId="149" pageNumber="150" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="149" pageNumber="150">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="149" pageNumber="150">
Undershrub with woody taproot, from which arise many rigid branched stems to c 40 cm, stems minutely adpressed pilose, the hairs resembling cystoliths. Leaves sessile, 10-30 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.5 mm, filiform, acute, adpressed pubescent. Flowers 1-3 in long-pedunculate, axillary and terminal dichasial cymes; peduncles up to 20 cm long, straight, slender and not very rigid; bracteoles 1-2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.25 mm, filiform; sepals 5-6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4 mm, obovate-elliptic, apiculate, glabrous; corolla1.4-1.5, colour unknown, midpetaline bands pubescent; ovary comose; style divided 2 mm above base; stigmas 3 mm. Capsule and seeds not known. [
<bibRefCitation author="Sa'ad, F" journalOrPublisher="Bronder Offset, Rotterdam" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" pagination="1 - 287" refId="B314" refString="Sa'ad, F, 1967. The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht. Bronder Offset, Rotterdam: 1 - 287" title="The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht" year="1967">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Sa’ad">Sa'ad</normalizedToken>
1967
</bibRefCitation>
: 97, 
<bibRefCitation author="Nowroozi, M" journalOrPublisher="Ministry of Jihad-e-Agriculture, Iran" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" pagination="1 - 110" refId="B244" refString="Nowroozi, M, 2002. Flora of Iran 40: Convolvulaceae. Ministry of Jihad-e-Agriculture, Iran: 1 - 110" title="Flora of Iran 40: Convolvulaceae" year="2002">Nowroozi 2002</bibRefCitation>
: 53 (plate), 102 (map)]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="149" pageNumber="150" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="149" pageNumber="150">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="149" pageNumber="150">
Iran (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="149" pageNumber="150">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Köie">Koeie</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
1302, 684).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="149" pageNumber="150" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="149" pageNumber="150">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="149" pageNumber="150">
Appears to be close to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boiss., Diagn. Pl. Orient. 7: 25. 1846. (Boissier" authorityYear="1846" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus leptocladus" order="Solanales" pageId="149" pageNumber="150" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="leptocladus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="149" pageNumber="150">Convolvulus leptocladus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but is distinguished by its filiform leaves, pubescent ovary and longer, oblong sepals.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
